===========
settings.py
-----------

INSTALLED_APPS = (
   ...
   'fogbugz_gadget'
)

TEMPLATE_CONTEXT_PROCESSORS = (
   ...
   'fogbugz_gadget.context_processors.forms',
)

# URL for submitting requests
FOG_API_ROOT = 'https://example.fogbugz.com/api.asp?'

FOG_PROJECT = 'Microsoft Windows'
FOG_PRIMARY_CONTACT = 'Steve Balmer'

# Submissions come from this user
FOG_EMAIL = 'steve@example.com'
FOG_PASSWORD = 'password'

=======
urls.py
-------

urlpatterns = patterns('',
    ...
    (r'^submit_bug$', 'fogbugz_gadget.views.submit_bug'),
)

====================
sample_template.html
--------------------

<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
    <head>
        ...
        <script src="{{ STATIC_URL }}testapp/js/jquery-1.6.min.js"></script>
        <script src="{{ STATIC_URL }}fogbugz_gadget/js/script.js"></script>
    </head>

    <body>
        ...
        {% include "fogbugz_gadget/submit_bug.html" %}
    </body>
</html>

===============
ADDITIONAL INFO
---------------
The FogBugz Gadget uses Django's cache framework. For best performance, configure your app's caching.

Error messages are also emailed to site admins, so make sure that's configurd properly.

To style the bug submission form, edit "fogbugz_gadget/static/fogbugz_gadget/css/style.css".
